text: Nichka-Bulyak () is a rural locality (a village) in Chukadybashevsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 41 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 48 km from Tuymazy, 10 km from Alexeyevka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Nichka-Bulyak
